'Ing ''Aka-Bo''' o '''Bo''' metung yang [[:en:extinct language|meteng]] amanung [[:en:Great Andamanese languages|Great Andamanese]], a kayabe kareng grupung pangulu (''Northern group''). Sadia yang magagamit king dakeng [[aslagan]] ning bebe dayatmalat (''east central coast'') ning [[:en:North Andaman|North Andaman]] ampo king Islang North Reef kareng [[:en:Andaman Islands|Kapuluan a Andaman]] (''Andaman Islands'') king [[India]]. Ing ''Aka-'' king umpisa ning lagiu ning amanu metung yang maralas magagamit a prefix a Great Andamanese par akareng pamalagiu (''noun'') a makaugne king [[dila]].<ref name=Templ>Temple, Richard C. (1902). ''A Grammar of the Andamanese Languages, being Chapter IV of Part I of the Census Report on the Andaman and Nicobar Islands''. Superintendent's Printing Press: Port Blair.</ref>

I Boa Sr., ing tauling taung atin pang atatandanan agiang ditak a Bo,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.andamanese.net/generalia.htm |title=GA Community |work=Vanishing Voices of the Great Andamanese (VOGA) |accessdate=2010-02-05}}</ref> mete ya aniang 26 Enero 2010, king edad a manga 85.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.andamanese.net/BoaSr_Obituary.html|title=Obituary for Boa Sr.|publisher=Vanishing Voices of the Great Andamanese (VOGA)|accessdate=2010-02-05}}</ref>

